## 1. Introduction

Step Radar respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how the app collects, uses, and protects information when you use the Step Radar mobile application.

By using Step Radar, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

## 2. Information We Collect

Step Radar may collect the following types of information:

### a. Step and Activity Data

The app may access step count and activity data from your device’s fitness sensors or health services in order to display and track your steps.

### b. Device Information

Basic device information such as device type, operating system version, and app version may be collected to help improve the app’s performance and stability.

### c. Optional Permissions

The app may request permissions such as:

* Physical activity / fitness data access (to count steps)

Step Radar only accesses the permissions necessary for the core functionality of the app.

## 3. How We Use Information

The collected information is used only to:

* Provide step tracking functionality
* Improve app performance and reliability
* Fix bugs and technical issues

Step Radar does **not sell or rent your personal data** to third parties.

## 4. Data Storage

Step data may be stored locally on your device. Step Radar does not intentionally store personal data on external servers unless required for app functionality.

## 5. Third-Party Services

Step Radar may use third-party services (such as analytics or app distribution platforms) that may collect anonymous usage information to help improve the application.

These services operate under their own privacy policies.

## 6. Children's Privacy

Step Radar is not specifically directed toward children under the age of 13. The app does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

## 7. Security

Reasonable measures are taken to protect information from unauthorized access, misuse, or disclosure.

However, no digital system can guarantee complete security.

## 8. Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Updates will be reflected by changing the effective date at the top of this document.

